  "text": "Traced 11 Java source files in sg-evals/kafka--0753c489 under clients/src/main/java/ that implement the producer record batch timeout path. The timeout is controlled by the delivery.timeout.ms configuration constant (DELIVERY_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG in ProducerConfig.java), validated in KafkaProducer.configureDeliveryTimeout(). RecordAccumulator.expiredBatches() scans partitions for batches that exceeded the delivery timeout via ProducerBatch.hasReachedDeliveryTimeout(). Sender.sendProducerData() calls expiredBatches() on each iteration, and Sender.getExpiredInflightBatches() checks in-flight batches separately. Failed batches are routed through Sender.failBatch() which calls ProducerBatch.completeExceptionally() with a new TimeoutException. The exception propagates through ProducerBatch.done() to ProduceRequestResult.error(), then to FutureRecordMetadata.valueOrError() (for synchronous callers) and Callback.onCompletion() (for asynchronous callers). TimeoutException extends RetriableException; the Errors.java enum maps REQUEST_TIMED_OUT to TimeoutException for protocol-level timeouts.",
